SIMPLE: dipteral
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dipteral
<hw>Dip"ter*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having two wings only; belonging to the order
Diptera.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anc. Arch.)</fld> <def>Having a double row of
columns on each on the flanks, as well as in front and rear; -- said of
a temple.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dipteran</ent>⟦br⟧
